    <exercise xml:id="exer_sec74-4">
      <introduction>
        <p>
          In each case, determine if the statement is true or false.
        </p>
      </introduction>

      <task>
        <statement>
        <p>
          For all <m>[ a ] \in \mathbb{Z}_6</m>,
          if <m>[ a ] \ne [ 0 ]</m>,
          then there exists a <m>[ b ] \in \mathbb{Z}_6</m> such that <m>[ a ] 
          \odot [ b ] = [ 1 ]</m>.
        </p>
        </statement>
        <answer>
          <p>
            The statement is false.
            By using the multiplication table for <m>\mathbb{Z}_6</m>,
            we see that a counterexample is <m>\left[ a \right] = \left[ 2 \right]</m>.
          </p>
        </answer>
      </task>
      <task>
        <statement>
        <p>
          For all <m>[ a ] \in \mathbb{Z}_5</m>,
          if <m>[ a ] \ne [ 0 ]</m>,
          then there exists a <m>[ b ] \in \mathbb{Z}_5</m> such that 
          <m>[ a ] \odot [ b ] = [ 1 ]</m>.
        </p>
        </statement>
        <answer>
          <p>
            The statement is true.
            By using the multiplication table for <m>\mathbb{Z}_5</m>,
            we see that:
            <md>
              <mrow>\left[ 1 \right] \amp \odot \left[ 1 \right] = \left[ 1 \right]. \amp 
              \left[ 2 \right] \amp \odot \left[ 3 \right] = \left[ 1 \right]</mrow>.
              <mrow>\left[ 3 \right] \amp \odot \left[ 2 \right] = \left[ 1 \right]. \amp 
              \left[ 4 \right] \amp \odot \left[ 4 \right] = \left[ 1 \right]</mrow>.
            </md>
          </p>
        </answer>
      </task>
    </exercise>

